  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "A RECENT earthquake at ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas Island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara, Cal.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", has revived interest in the story of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the old Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who led a Crusoe life on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for many years. She was left there by accident in 1836, and her existence forgotton until twenty years later, when ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a Santa Barbara hunter",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had visited ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for otters, found her there and carried her to ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She had entirely forgotten her language, and in consequence the story of her hermitage was never known. Three months after her rescue she died, and was buried by ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mission fathers",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
